<head> 
<title>Modal</title> 
<style> 
.container { 
height: 100vh; 
width: 100vw; 
background-color: tomato; 
position: relative; 
} 
.modal { 
 height: 350px; 
width: 500px; 
background-color: lightseagreen; 
position: absolute; 
top: 20%; 
left: 10%; 
} 
.hide { 
display: none; 
} 
</style> 
</head> 
<body> 
<div class="container"> 
<button class="open">click here to open</button> 
<div class="modal hide"> 
<h1>Modal</h1> 
 
<p>The modal class defines a container for a modal.<br> 
 The modal-content class defines the modal content.<br> 
 
 Modal content can be any HTML element (divs, headings, paragraphs, images, 
etc.). 
 </p> 
 <h2>close a modal</h2> 
 <p>To close a modal, add the w3-button class to an element together with an 
onclick attribute that points to the id of the modal (id01). </p> 
 <img src="jsimg.jpg" alt="jsimg"> 
<button class="close">click here to close</button> 
</div> 
</div> 
<script> 
const openBtn = document.querySelector(".open"); 
const closeBtn = document.querySelector(".close"); 
const modal = document.querySelector(".modal"); 
openBtn.addEventListener("click", function () { 
modal.classList.remove("hide"); 
}); 
closeBtn.addEventListener("click", function () { 
modal.classList.add("hide"); 
}); 
</script> 
</body> 
</html>
